div.div: This pull request introduces updates to the pyproject.toml configuration file and refactors several Python modules within the ezpz project. Key changes include dependency adjustments, logging improvements, and the addition of new dataclasses for model and data arguments. Additionally, there are updates to streamline code readability and enhance functionality. Configuration Changes: Added new classifiers to pyproject.toml for improved metadata and compatibility declarations. Replaced sentencepiece dependency with torchinfo and updated optional dependencies for development and documentation. [1] [2] Adjusted line-length settings in pyproject.toml to 79 and added a pycodestyle configuration for Ruff linting. [1] [2] Logging and Environment Updates: Simplified logging level configurations and environment variable assignments in src/ezpz/__init__.py . [1] [2] Commented out DeepSpeed import and related warnings to avoid runtime issues when the library is unavailable. Model and Data Argument Enhancements: Introduced HFModelArguments and HFDataTrainingArguments dataclasses in src/ezpz/configs.py to streamline the handling of Hugging Face model and dataset configurations. Code Refactoring: Replaced the custom Network class in src/ezpz/examples/minimal.py with SequentialLinearNet from ezpz.models.minimal for improved modularity. [1] [2] Added model summary functionality to provide detailed insights during setup.
